    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Tirmilyra sagittifera (Alcock, 1896) n. comb., paralectotype female (CL 6.0 mm, CW 5.7 mm) (ZSI C910/10) Karachi, Pakistan: (A) frontal view of cephalothorax; (B) female gonopore (right side); Tirmilyra concinnus (Ghani & Tirmizi, 1995) n. comb., fresh female (CL 9.4 mm, CW 8.4 mm) (ZUTC 6925) Hormoz Island, Persian Gulf: (C) frontal view of cephalothorax; (D) female gonopore (right side)." ;
